NFL games available with NFL Sunday Ticket

NFL Sunday Ticket is a premium sports package bringing you all Sunday afternoon (Eastern Time) regular season National Football League (NFL) games that are not carried on local broadcasts in your area.

There are two ways to purchase NFL Sunday Ticket:

  • As an add-on to a YouTube TV Base Plan
  • As an individual Primetime Channel on YouTube

In this article, you’ll learn what games are available with each NFL Sunday Ticket package option. If you're already a subscriber, find what games are airing this Sunday in your area.

NFL Sunday Ticket package options

NFL Sunday Ticket includes Sunday afternoon (Eastern Time) NFL games that aren’t available on your local broadcasts during the NFL regular season. So if you’re a Dallas Cowboys fan in Miami, you can watch all of the Sunday Cowboys games that aren’t shown on NBC, CBS, or FOX in your area.

NFL games available on YouTube TV with the NFL Sunday Ticket add-on

YouTube TV is a live TV streaming service with 100+ channels. A YouTube TV Base Plan is $82.99 per month. With a YouTube TV Base Plan, you can watch:

  • Preseason games
  • Regular season games, including:
    • Sunday Night Football on NBC
    • Thanksgiving games on CBS, NBC, and FOX
    • Monday Night Football on ESPN
    • NFL Network and ABC games
  • Postseason games

When you add NFL Sunday Ticket to your YouTube TV Base Plan, you can also watch all out-of-market Sunday games throughout the regular season. Combining a YouTube TV Base Plan with the NFL Sunday Ticket add-on means you can watch:

Preseason NFL games

  • Watch preseason NFL games on NFL Network, ESPN, or local ABC, CBS, Fox, and NBC channels with your YouTube TV Base Plan. To see what channels are available in your area, enter your zip code on the YouTube TV welcome page.
    • Note: If a preseason game in your local area is airing on a local channel and NFL Network, it will be subject to embargo and not shown on NFL Network, even if the local channel is not available as part of the YouTube TV Base Plan in your area. Most preseason games are re-aired at later dates and times on NFL Network though, and these rebroadcasts are not subject to the same restrictions.
  • NFL Sunday Ticket does not include preseason games.
  • Thursday Night Football on Amazon Prime is not available on YouTube TV.

Regular season NFL games on local & national channels

  • Watch regular season NFL games carried nationally, like Sunday Night Football on NBC and Monday Night Football on ESPN, and locally on CBS and Fox channels included in your YouTube TV Base Plan.
  • Thursday Night Football on Amazon Prime is not available on YouTube TV.

Regular season Sunday afternoon (Eastern Time) out-of-market NFL games

Watch regular season Sunday afternoon (Eastern Time) games carried on CBS and Fox on channels not available in your local area with NFL Sunday Ticket. NFL Sunday Ticket starts with the regular season in September.

Postseason NFL games

  • Watch postseason games carried nationally on CBS, Fox, ESPN, and NBC with your YouTube Base Plan.
  • NFL Sunday Ticket does not include postseason games.

NFL games available on NFL Sunday Ticket through Primetime Channel

YouTube Primetime Channels offer individual streaming services, like NFL Sunday Ticket, for watching movies, TV shows, and live content all on YouTube without a YouTube TV Base Plan subscription.

With the NFL Sunday Ticket on Primetime Channels, you can stream out-of-market NFL regular season Sunday afternoon games (Eastern Time) on CBS and Fox, starting in September.

Note: NFL Sunday Ticket does not include preseason and postseason games.
